        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Oct 10<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I received long ago your extremely obliging letter of June 15<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>,<ref target="#foot.f2"/> Occasionally numbers of the Bot. Bulletin are sent me by some one by <hi rend="underline">Post</hi>, &amp; I have <hi rend="underline">always</hi> looked through them; but I am sorry to say that I have never received a number with any account of Apocynum.<ref target="#foot.f3"/> There seems often to be great delay in the transit of parcels by the Smithsonian Institute.<ref target="#foot.f4"/></p>
<p>With my best wishes for the success of your future observations— | Believe me Yours faithfully | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the reference to Leggett’s papers on <hi rend="italic">Apocynum</hi> (see n. 3, below).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Leggett’s letter to CD has not been found.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">Leggett wrote five brief articles on the fertilisation of <hi rend="italic">Apocynum androsaemifolium</hi> (fly-trap dogbane or spreading dogbane) in the <hi rend="italic">Bulletin of the Torrey Botanical Club</hi>, of which he was editor, between October 1872 and June 1873 (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_4662.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Leggett 1872–3</ref>).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">The Torrey Botanical Club had no formal connection with the <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4438.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Smithsonian Institution</ref>. In January 1872, CD had received a book through the Smithsonian that had been requested on his behalf in August 1871 (see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 19, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7891.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from L. H. Morgan, 1 August 1871</ref>, and <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 20, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8167.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to L. H. Morgan, 20 January 1872</ref>).</note>
        </div>        
            
